T*
(## Project Summary) Tj
T*
(SmartCampus Companion is a simple Flutter + FastAPI campus app built for a mobile operating) Tj
T*
(systems assignment. The goal is to demonstrate the required OS concepts with a small,) Tj
T*
(functional app rather than a production-grade system.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Implemented Features) Tj
T*
(- Authentication with login and logout flow.) Tj
T*
(- Announcements, events, and timetable screens backed by API data.) Tj
T*
(- Offline caching for core data using SQLite.) Tj
T*
(- Persistent settings using SharedPreferences.) Tj
T*
(- Minimal device-feature demo screen for camera/gallery and location.) Tj
T*
(- Local notification test trigger from Settings.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(## Mobile OS Concept Mapping) Tj
T*
(| Feature | Mobile OS Concept | What the App Demonstrates |) Tj
T*
(|---|---|---|) Tj
T*
(| Login and logout | Lifecycle and security | Session-based access to the app with) Tj
T*
(authenticated navigation. |) Tj
T*
(| API data loading | Networking | REST calls to backend endpoints for announcements, events,) Tj
T*
(and timetable. |) Tj
T*
(| SQLite cache | Storage and sandboxing | Local persistence for offline access and cached) Tj
T*
(loading states. |) Tj
T*
(| Settings storage | Storage and sandboxing | Simple preference persistence across app) Tj
T*
(restarts. |) Tj
T*
(| Device features screen | Permissions model | Camera/gallery and location permission) Tj
T*
(requests with fallback states. |) Tj
T*
(| Notification test | Notifications | A basic local notification path that can be triggered) Tj
T*
(from the app. |) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
